Unless your killing mobs in under 1 minute or so, it's impossible for you to not grab aggro. Kiting around in PoT/PoV/whatever, there wasn't 1 pet that escaped death from a mob after landing shit like Blood of Thule (extreme high aggro) Cessatation of Cor (sp?), Embracing darkness and list goes on. I can chain cast those and still have pet eat it. But like I addressed near the end of the rant, &quot;maybe one day they'll fix it&quot;, and heck...they did! Yay for me! err all Necro brother's and sister. Were up 2 to 4 now.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>They may have nerfed CoD charming to shit, but charms in general are still viable for necro. I have tested the possesseds in AC both solo and duo using both ToB and clicky Terrorclaw shoulders and had no prob clearing the entire 12ish spawns before repops. Not saying they shouldn't fix lvl 65 charm to m-50 or something or give us an undead-only tash type spell, but from my tests so far this nerf really only affects maybe a half dozen necros on the server who farmed CoD not the class as a whole.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
